      • addInstructioncode

        public void addInstructioncode(java.lang.CharSequence param)
        Appends the specified Instructioncode to the end of the collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Specifies the Instruction Code for the payment.

        1. Time Indicator codes (13C) start with the pre-fix 'TI-' 2. Instruction Codes (23E) start with the pre-fix 'IC-' 3. Sender to Receiver information codes (72) start the pre-fix 'SR-' 4. Regulatory Reporting codes (77B) start with the pre-fix 'RR-'

        Allowed Values: If CTR/BTR indicator (Transfer Type) = C (CTR) allowed values are Tag 13C/23E/72/77B If CTR/BTR indicator (Transfer Type) = B (BTR) allowed values are Tag 13C/72

        Syntax : (TI-) Allowed format: TI-/Code/Text (IC-) Allowed format: IC-Code[/Text] (SR-) 1 line must be in format: SR-/Code/[Text] (SR-) Allowed format: SR-/Code/[Text] or SR-//Text (RR-) 1 line must be in format: RR-/Code/XX[//Text] (RR-) Allowed format:RR-/Code/XX[//Text] or RR-//Text

        Multi Value Field.

        Parameters:
        param - the Instructioncode to append
        Returns:
        nothing

        public TField getCreditvaluedateimposedflag()
        Returns the Creditvaluedateimposedflag

        Field description: This field specifies whether the credit value date is imposed or can still be overwritten by the date component. In case the impose flag is lacking but the credit value date is specified, the manual input is more a suggestion towards the system. In case the impose flag is present and the credit value date is specified, the manual input is a hard requirement to be taken into account by the date component, even though the given date is a non-working day.

      • getDebitvaluedateimposedflag

        public TField getDebitvaluedateimposedflag()
        Returns the Debitvaluedateimposedflag

        Field description: This field specifies whether the debit value date is imposed or can still be overwritten by the date component. In case the impose flag is lacking but the debit value date is specified, the manual input is more a suggestion towards the system. In case the impose flag is present and the debit value date is specified, the manual input is a hard requirement to be taken into account by the date component, even though the given date is a non-working day.

        Check Box Field.

        Possible values: "Y" " "

        Parameters:
        Returns:

      • getInstructioncode

        public TField getInstructioncode(int idx)
        Returns the Instructioncode at the specified position in this collection.

        Field description: Specifies the Instruction Code for the payment.

        1. Time Indicator codes (13C) start with the pre-fix 'TI-' 2. Instruction Codes (23E) start with the pre-fix 'IC-' 3. Sender to Receiver information codes (72) start the pre-fix 'SR-' 4. Regulatory Reporting codes (77B) start with the pre-fix 'RR-'

        Allowed Values: If CTR/BTR indicator (Transfer Type) = C (CTR) allowed values are Tag 13C/23E/72/77B If CTR/BTR indicator (Transfer Type) = B (BTR) allowed values are Tag 13C/72

        Syntax : (TI-) Allowed format: TI-/Code/Text (IC-) Allowed format: IC-Code[/Text] (SR-) 1 line must be in format: SR-/Code/[Text] (SR-) Allowed format: SR-/Code/[Text] or SR-//Text (RR-) 1 line must be in format: RR-/Code/XX[//Text] (RR-) Allowed format:RR-/Code/XX[//Text] or RR-//Text

        Multi Value Field.

        Parameters:
        idx - idx of the element to return
        Returns:
        TField -

      • insertInstructioncode

        public void insertInstructioncode(TField param, int pos)
        Insert the specified Instructioncode to the specified position in the collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Specifies the Instruction Code for the payment.

        1. Time Indicator codes (13C) start with the pre-fix 'TI-' 2. Instruction Codes (23E) start with the pre-fix 'IC-' 3. Sender to Receiver information codes (72) start the pre-fix 'SR-' 4. Regulatory Reporting codes (77B) start with the pre-fix 'RR-'

        Allowed Values: If CTR/BTR indicator (Transfer Type) = C (CTR) allowed values are Tag 13C/23E/72/77B If CTR/BTR indicator (Transfer Type) = B (BTR) allowed values are Tag 13C/72

        Syntax : (TI-) Allowed format: TI-/Code/Text (IC-) Allowed format: IC-Code[/Text] (SR-) 1 line must be in format: SR-/Code/[Text] (SR-) Allowed format: SR-/Code/[Text] or SR-//Text (RR-) 1 line must be in format: RR-/Code/XX[//Text] (RR-) Allowed format:RR-/Code/XX[//Text] or RR-//Text

        Multi Value Field.

        Parameters:
        param - the Instructioncode to append
        pos - The position where to insert the value.
        Returns:
        nothing

      • removeInstructioncode

        public void removeInstructioncode(int idx)
        Remove the Instructioncode at the specified position in this collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Specifies the Instruction Code for the payment.

        1. Time Indicator codes (13C) start with the pre-fix 'TI-' 2. Instruction Codes (23E) start with the pre-fix 'IC-' 3. Sender to Receiver information codes (72) start the pre-fix 'SR-' 4. Regulatory Reporting codes (77B) start with the pre-fix 'RR-'

        Allowed Values: If CTR/BTR indicator (Transfer Type) = C (CTR) allowed values are Tag 13C/23E/72/77B If CTR/BTR indicator (Transfer Type) = B (BTR) allowed values are Tag 13C/72

        Syntax : (TI-) Allowed format: TI-/Code/Text (IC-) Allowed format: IC-Code[/Text] (SR-) 1 line must be in format: SR-/Code/[Text] (SR-) Allowed format: SR-/Code/[Text] or SR-//Text (RR-) 1 line must be in format: RR-/Code/XX[//Text] (RR-) Allowed format:RR-/Code/XX[//Text] or RR-//Text

        Multi Value Field.

        Parameters:
        idx - index of the element to remove
        Returns:
        nothing

        Set the specified value for Credittreasuryrate
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Defines the rate at which the Treasury unit will buy or sell foreign Currency from/to the marketing units. The Final exchange rate quoted to Customers (Customer Rate) will be determined by the addition or subtraction of the appropriate Customer Spread to/from the Treasury Buy/Sell Rate. This value can only be imposed if the Exchange/Customer Rate is not imposed. If not imposed the value that is entered will be ignored and taken from T24 Currency table.

      • setCreditvaluedateimposedflag

        public void setCreditvaluedateimposedflag(TField value)
        Set the specified value for Creditvaluedateimposedflag
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field specifies whether the credit value date is imposed or can still be overwritten by the date component. In case the impose flag is lacking but the credit value date is specified, the manual input is more a suggestion towards the system. In case the impose flag is present and the credit value date is specified, the manual input is a hard requirement to be taken into account by the date component, even though the given date is a non-working day.

        Check Box Field.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setDebitvaluedateimposedflag

        public void setDebitvaluedateimposedflag(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for Debitvaluedateimposedflag
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field specifies whether the debit value date is imposed or can still be overwritten by the date component. In case the impose flag is lacking but the debit value date is specified, the manual input is more a suggestion towards the system. In case the impose flag is present and the debit value date is specified, the manual input is a hard requirement to be taken into account by the date component, even though the given date is a non-working day.

        Check Box Field.

        Possible values: "Y" " "

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setInstructioncode

        public void setInstructioncode(TField param, int idx)
        Set the specified Instructioncode to a specific position in collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Specifies the Instruction Code for the payment.

        1. Time Indicator codes (13C) start with the pre-fix 'TI-' 2. Instruction Codes (23E) start with the pre-fix 'IC-' 3. Sender to Receiver information codes (72) start the pre-fix 'SR-' 4. Regulatory Reporting codes (77B) start with the pre-fix 'RR-'

        Allowed Values: If CTR/BTR indicator (Transfer Type) = C (CTR) allowed values are Tag 13C/23E/72/77B If CTR/BTR indicator (Transfer Type) = B (BTR) allowed values are Tag 13C/72

        Syntax : (TI-) Allowed format: TI-/Code/Text (IC-) Allowed format: IC-Code[/Text] (SR-) 1 line must be in format: SR-/Code/[Text] (SR-) Allowed format: SR-/Code/[Text] or SR-//Text (RR-) 1 line must be in format: RR-/Code/XX[//Text] (RR-) Allowed format:RR-/Code/XX[//Text] or RR-//Text

        Multi Value Field.

        Parameters:
        param - the Instructioncode to append
        idx - the position in collection
        Returns:
        nothing

        public void setStatus(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for Status
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Indicates the Status Code (a Numeric number between 0 - 999) of the payment that is currently being processed.

After successful Final Authorize Action, the Status is changed to 600.
